cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper focuses on optimizing the operations of multiplying a matrix with the transpose of another matrix, which is a common operation in deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the use of GPUs, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for matrix transpose, which could fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
